	     </form></table>
<tr><td colspan=2><ul>
<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f1076010873638723335>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=4&mid=1076010873638723335>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=4&mid=1076010873638723335>kiting</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=4&mid=1076010873638723335#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Feb 5th 2:54 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=216396><span id= >Rorgg</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>One of the most useful types you're going to run into is Swarm (or Charm) Kiting.<br><br>Lineup:<br>4 x DoT chant<br>Selo's Accelerating Chorus<br>Charm<br>Snare (this can vary, I like snare here)<br>Invis (make this SSoT when you get it to cut down on instrument swapping unless you have the epic)<br><br>Note: Set your target swap key for this.&nbsp;&nbsp;By default it's unset.  What the key does is toggle to your previous target.<br><br>Pull 3, 4, 12 mobs (don't laugh, the Werewolf camp in PoNightmare is great for this until you get the 64 charm, and it's got around 10 mobs).  Just run around in circles until they're kind of tightly packed.  Now, pick one and charm it.  Pick another (F8 works fine) and hit your pet attack hotkey.<br><br>One of 3 things will happen:<br><br>A. Pet can't catch target.<br>B. Pet hits target and most or all of the others keep chasing you<br>C. Pet hits target and all the others jump on your pet (good!).<br><br>If A happens, you can either toss one pulse of Snare on target, or just keep running in tight circles, until they fight.  Our snare's low aggro, so it works well for this.<br><br>If B happens, or after A and the pack's still chasing you, you need to basically kite the pack smack dab over your pet so they'll aggro him.<br><br>Ok, so now all the mobs are attacking your poor pet.  This next one is the bit that takes practice: you want to invis so that charm breaks when your pet is at something like 10% HP, then just chant it down from there.  You don't want to be kiting it forever, and you don't want it to die, so the timing is tricky, depending on the mobs involved, and how many of them there are.  You can do this with the Invis song (needs a flute), SSoT (still a drum, so that's nice, though you have to reapply SAC after), or some kind of self-clicky invis.  Two options on that are the Goblin Gazughi Ring or the Tiny Cloak of Darkest Night.<br><br>Anyway, you chant down your pet, it dies, now hit that toggle key to get the one he was beating on, charm him, and repeat the process.  Why the toggle key?  Because if you're looting or something and charm breaks, getting back your original pet on target makes things a lot easier.<br><br>Anyway, keep this up until you get down to 2 and one runs, then break charm and chant both to death.  Once you get good at it you'll know if you can toss extra DoTs in toward the end or not, and how to get mobs to &quot;stick&quot; better, but that varies per mob type.  The real key is to keep your aggro as small as possible, so the pack will go after your pet.  That's why SAC is so big -- if you're effectively buffing yourself with Selo's Accelerando every 6 seconds, it adds aggro on you.<br><br>Good luck!</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
