<table border=0 cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>
	     <table class=mform  border=0 cellpadding=1 cellspacing=0 width=100%>
	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f1076011576643304890>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=4&mid=1076011576643304890>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=4&mid=1076011576643304890>meditate</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=4&mid=1076011576643304890#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Thu, Feb 5th 3:06 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=216396><span id= >Rorgg</span></a><br><span id=notbold>3 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Bards do get the meditate skill automatically (I think it's during your first zone after level 10), solely for the purpose of memorizing songs more quickly.<br><br>Bard mana regeneration is a natural 1 per tick, and this never increases (even sitting down has no effect).&nbsp;&nbsp;Mana regeneration buffs like Clarity, KEI, Spiritual Dominion, Protection of the 9, even bard mana regen songs have no effect on the bard's mana pool.  The only things that do effect it are AA abilities (Mental Clarity) and worn mana regen (Flowing Thought).  FT I literally doubles a bard's mana regeneration.<br><br>With this limitation, fortunately almost all songs have no mana cost.  The ones that do are Denon's Desperate Dirge, a targetted AE DD song at level 43 that's usually not worth a spell gem, and your level 39 and 64 charm songs.  The bard AA ability Fading Memories also has a large mana cost to it.<br><br>So there's plenty a bard can do without mana, but FM and charm are fairly key abilities pulling and soloing respectively so eventually you'll want to get some flowing thought eventually.</p>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
