	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=61546><span id=Sage>Slipskin</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>1154 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.80]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Swarming indoors is a bad idea.&nbsp;&nbsp;Yes, the other mobs will go after your new pet but there needs to be a decent amount of distance between you and them first.  Hard to do indoors.  By the time your pet pulls off the aggro you have a good chance of being a bloody mess.<br><br>However, I agree, LDoN was made for bards.  Lull (especially now that it lasts 30 sec) the extras (pray for no resists) and single pull.  If you overpull, no problem. Mezz the adds. Hard to mezz more than 3 at a time since bard mezz only lasts 18 secs at your level. The same with charm song.  Nothing like an overpull to keep your fingers and cursor busy.  One little slip up and BAM! Wipe out!  It makes you nervous as hell but when you pull it off the feeling of satisfaction just can't be beat.  Your whole party is impressed and just loves you.  &quot;Wow! I never thought a bard could do that!&quot;  <br><br>More and more folks are realizing the value of bards in LDoN.</p>&nbsp;<br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=104222</a><br><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=479760</a></td></tr>
