	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=classes2.html?class=4&mid=1073306440215304318>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=classes2.html?class=4&mid=1073306440215304318>Armor</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes2.html?class=4&mid=1073306440215304318#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Mon, Jan 5th 7:40 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=223932><span id=Scholar>Aarenla</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>82 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.05]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>If you are looking for a full set of SS armor and are looking to farm it all yourself it is going to take you quite some time. The items are not no drop so it may be easier to just farm cash and buy them rather then camping all the mobs. Some of the mobs are easier then others but you will have to kill Trak and Venril Sathir if you want to farm them yourself. Keep in mind also that Trak and Venril Sathir don't drop them every time either. Below is a list of where SS items drop:<br><br>SS BP - Trak is the only mob who drops it I believe. I have been on several Trak raids and seen it drop once.<br><br>SS Greaves - Venril Sathir boss of KC. Again I have seen VS dropped several times and have actually never seen them drop.<br><br>SS Boots - Drolvarg Guardians and Sentries in Karnor's. These are a bit more common but still it will take quite some time for you to see them drop.<br><br>SS Helm - Froggy in Old Seb. He is named mob (Like level 50 or maybe a bit higher). He's not always up and has a PH so good luck.<br><br>SS Vambraces - Froglok Repairer in Old Seb.<br><br>SS Bracer - Froglok Armorer in Old Seb.<br><br>SS Gauntlets - Skeletal lookout in Karnor's.<br><br>All but the BP and Greaves can be gotten with a good solid high 50s group. Trak of course takes a good size raid and Venril Sathir can be done with a solid group of high 50s low sixties as long as you have a good solid tank and good solid healer. Good luck on getting all pieces to drop for you though.</p>&nbsp;<br>Of his knowledge a man should never boast,<br>Rather be sparing of speach<br>When to his house a wiser comes:<br>Seldom do those who are silent make mistakes;<br>Mother wit is ever a faithful freind.</td></tr>
