	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=4283><span id= >Tassoth, Eater of Souls</span></a><br><span id=notbold>311 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default [2.06]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>What you will notice is that songs have an upper limit in which they can be affected by an instrument. So where as a song such as &quot;Requiem of Time&quot; may well slow a mob for 52% with an instrument you may find this is then max'd out at 60% (example).<br>This means your songs are more effective but not quite as effective as the 3 proper slowing classes.<br><br>Hope this helps a bit.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </p>&nbsp;<br>Maylian Ap'Aurelius (Veeshan)<br>Iksar Beastlord 65th lvl<br>I know what I AM, But What are YOU!! </td></tr>
