	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=4283><span id= >Tassoth, Eater of Souls</span></a><br><span id=notbold>311 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [2.63]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>You can solo at level 12, or I did on my bard in paludal caverns shadeweavers side. Although you're a bit beyond that, I would suggest that you carry on grouping maybe in Highkeep, this is bacause you'll get exp faster than you can kite it and also since it will help hone those twisting skills you need to become a good bard. You wouldn't believe how many 60+ Bards I see just singing one song, and even then its not likely to be a usefull one (i.e villa's verses of celerity in a group with spell haste)<br><br>I took my bard to PoN at level 47 and solo'd there happily although it took a while to kill mobs. I grouped in Justice for a while but in the end went back to Dulaks Harbour (LoY expansion) and swarm kited there, exp is very nice there and I got up to 1/4 - 1/2 a level if I pulled a large swarm.<br><br>If you need to single target pull a mob with possible add's you need to target the mob and then start singing lull, you'll then get a message saying &quot;soandso feels sad&quot;. Do all mobs that are likely to agro you on pull, then pull the mob you want.<br><br><a href="http://www.EQDiva.com" target=_new>http://www.EQDiva.com</a> and <a href="http://www.dotnetdiva.com" target=_new>http://www.dotnetdiva.com</a> should help on guides.<br><br>Hope this post helps</p>&nbsp;<br>Maylian Ap'Aurelius (Veeshan)<br>Iksar Beastlord 65th lvl<br>I know what I AM, But What are YOU!! </td></tr>
